    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-28T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-28T23:00:00-05:00" n="118"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6625: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ballantine</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-29T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 29, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 29—7:28
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consuls at Canton have received for transmission a declaration dated April 27 by
                    the Southwest Political Council addressed to the League of Nations and to the
                    Ministers of the signatory powers of the Nine-Power Pact. This declaration
                    asserts that the statement of policy issued by the Japanese Foreign Office on
                    April 17 threatens the independence of China and the peace of the Far East and
                    it calls upon the League and the parties to the Nine-Power Treaty to discharge
                    their obligations under existing instruments aimed at maintaining international
                    peace.</p>
                <pb facs="0238" n="148" xml:id="pg_148"/>
                <p>Copies by mail.<note n="79" xml:id="d118fn79">Not printed.</note> Repeated to the
                    Department, the Legation and Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ballantine</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
